article.headline: Cleveland St. 76, Loyola of Chicago 50
article.story: CLEVELAND -- J'Nathan Bullock scored 20 points and was 3-for-3 on 3-pointers as Cleveland St. beat Loyola of Chicago 76-50 Thursday night in Horizon League play. Trevon Harmon added 17 points, including four 3-pointers, for the Vikings (12-5, 3-2). George Tandy chipped in 13 points from off the bench, going 5-for-5 on free throws. Cedric Jackson contributed eight assists. J.R. Blount scored 16 points for the Ramblers (9-7, 1-3). The Vikings scored the first 8 points and never lost the lead, pulling to a 48-26 advantage at the break. They were ahead by as many as 29 points in the second half. The Vikings outshot the Ramblers 46.3 percent to 32.2 percent from the field, and also held the advantage in 3-pointers (52.9 percent) and free throws (81 percent). Loyola performed better at the boards, with 41 rebounds, including 19 on offense for 18 second-chance points.
